.TH AI-PLAYBOOK-MAN 1 "" "ai-playbook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai\-playbook\-man \- Install or remove the man pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBai\-playbook\fR man <install|uninstall> [\-\-to <dir>] [\-\-force]
.SH DESCRIPTION
man serves the manual pages rendered at RUNTIME from the same command
registry this help text comes from, so the installed pages always match
the running binary. Meant for `go install` users — the release archives
and the Homebrew formula already ship/install them.
.PP
man install [\-\-to <dir>] [\-\-force]
    Write the ai\-playbook overview page, one page per command, and ask's
    page into <dir>, creating it as needed. Default <dir>:
    $XDG_DATA_HOME/man/man1 (~/.local/share/man/man1), which `man` finds
    via the standard PATH\-derived manpath on most systems. Existing files
    are never overwritten without \-\-force.
.PP
man uninstall [\-\-to <dir>]
    Remove exactly the pages install writes; already\-absent pages are
    skipped (idempotent — safe as a package post\-uninstall hook).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR \fI<dir>\fR
target directory instead of $XDG_DATA_HOME/man/man1 (install/uninstall)
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
overwrite already\-installed man pages (install)
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
ai\-playbook man install
.fi
.PP
.nf
ai\-playbook man uninstall
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBai\-playbook\fR(1)
